---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import authorPhoto from "../assets/images/author-site-photo-2.png";
---

<Layout>
  <section
    class="flex flex-col justify-start md:justify-center items-center gap-12 w-full mt-52 pb-28 md:pb-0 px-12 font-sans text-md text-left">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">About</h2>
    <div
      class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-center items-center gap-6 w-full md:px-12 lg:w-[900px]">
      <img
        class="md:w-1/2 object-cover"
        id="author-photo"
        src={authorPhoto.src}
        alt=""
        fetchpriority="high"
      />
      <div class="md:w-1/2">
        <p>
          Jack Thacker grew up on a farm in Herefordshire and is now based in
          Bristol, UK.
        </p>
        <br />
        <p>
          His poetry has appeared in magazines such as <i>Magma</i>, <i
            >PN Review</i
          >, <i>Stand</i>,
          <i>Blackbox Manifold</i>, <i>The Clearing</i> and <i
            >Caught by the River</i
          > and has been broadcast on BBC Radio.
        </p>
        <br />
        <p>
          He was the winner of the Charles Causley International Poetry
          Competition and has been the writer in residence at both the Museum of
          English Rural Life and Lighthouse Arts Centre.
        </p>
        <br />
        <p>
          His debut pamphlet-length collection is <i>Handling</i>, which came
          out with Two Rivers Press in 2018.
        </p>
        <br />
        <p>
          He is currently preparing a full-length collection of poems for
          publication.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
